            <paragraph>The <strong>bool</strong> is a built-in <reference internal="True" refuri="class_variant#class-variant"><inline classes="std std-ref">Variant</inline></reference> type that may only store one of two values: <literal>true</literal> or <literal>false</literal>. You can imagine it as a switch that can be either turned on or off, or as a binary digit that can either be 1 or 0.</paragraph>
